Description: Revert query_exists vfunc and ignore_trash_mount to 2.80 behavior
 The GLib 2.84 release introduced a new query_exists vfunc in GFileIface that
 changes how g_file_query_exists() works. Instead of going through
 g_file_query_info() (which does a full stat), it now dispatches to a
 file-type-specific vfunc. For GLocalFile, this uses faccessat().
 .
 This behavioral change causes the 360 browser's Save As functionality to
 fail. The root cause is likely that the vfunc dispatch changes the error
 handling or return semantics in a way that breaks Chromium-based file
 dialogs in sandboxed environments.
 .
 Additionally, the ignore_trash_mount() logic was reversed in 2.84, changing
 the default behavior for trash detection on mount points.
 .
 Fix by reverting both changes to match GLib 2.80.1-1deepin4 behavior:
 - Remove query_exists vfunc dispatch from g_file_query_exists()
 - Remove g_local_file_query_exists() function and registration
 - Revert ignore_trash_mount() logic to check system_internal first
Author: Codex Agent <codex@deepin.org>
